interested in more details about this particular work.  The discipline and country mentioned behind a researcher's name is merely the one where they got their basic degree, not in general the one of their present work. In practice, all subjects fall within the broad, transdisciplinary domain of  <a href="EVOLCYB.html">evolutionary cybernetics</a>, or what I might summarize as: the self-organization and evolution  of distributed, cognitive systems. <p>Most of this research is being done within the new <a href="http://ecco.vub.ac.be">ECCO group</a> that I direct. I advise the others more from a distance, as their main affiliation is elsewhere.<p><h2>Within ECCO</h2><dl><Dt><b><img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://memetics.chielens.net/">Klaas Chielens</a></b> (linguistics, Belgium):<Dd> started 2004, subject "<a href="/Papers/Project-Klaas.pdf">Evolutionary Aspects of Language Spreading</a>: Quantitative Research of Memetic Selection Processes in the Distribution of Virus hoaxes"  <Dt><b> <img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://www.mixel.be">Mixel Kiemen</a></b> (computer science, Belgium) :<Dd> simulation of innovation by agents learning to "improperly" use objects, thus discovering new functions and "appropriating" parts of the environment<Dt><b><img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://www.soe.ucsc.edu/~okram">Marko Rodriguez</a></b> (computer science, USA) <Dd>development of societal-scale decision-supportsystem capable of tapping the collective intelligence potential of asociety<dt><b><a href="http://clement.vidal.philosophons.com/">Cl&eacute;ment Vida</a>l </b>(philosophy, France)</dt><dt class="rteindent1">evolutionary theories of cosmology</dt><dt><b><img alt="" src="Images/externallink.GIF" /><a target="_blank" style="text-decoration: none; font-weight: bold; color: rgb(136, 136, 34); " href="http://www.shwetambara.com">Shwetambhara Sabharwal</a></b>&nbsp;(psychology, India)<br type="_moz" /></dt><dt class="rteindent1">influence of relations and emotions on cognitive categorization<br type="_moz" /><Dt><b><img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://pespmc1.vub.ac.be:8000/ECCO-Web/Erden">Erden G&ouml;ktepe</a></b> (political science, Turkey) <Dd>complexity and self-organization theories applied to the emergence of new actors and institutions in international relations</dl></dl><h2>Former</h2><DL><Dt><b><img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://homepages.vub.ac.be/~cgershen/">Carlos Gershenson</a></b> (computer science, Mexico):<Dd> started 2002, defended 2007, subject: "<img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://www.vub.ac.be/docop/abstracts/publish/72551.htm">Design and Control of Self-organizing Systems</a>" (co-promotor with <img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://www.vub.ac.be/CLEA/aerts/">D. Aerts</a>) <Dt><b> <img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://www.cs.odu.edu/~jbollen">Johan Bollen</a></b> (psychology, Belgium):<Dd> thesis "<img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://www.cs.odu.edu/~jbollen/diss.html">A Cognitive Model of Adaptive Web Design and Navigation</a>: a shared knowledge perspective", started 1994, defended 2001 (co-promotor <img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://www.vub.ac.be/PESP/VanOverwalle.html">F. Van Overwalle</a>). Since Jan. 2002, Johan heads his own research groep at the Old Dominion University, in Virginia, USA.<Dt><b><img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://home2.pi.be/ping1796/">Bertin Martens</a></b> (economics, Belgium): <Dd>thesis "<img src=Images/externallink.GIF><a TARGET=_blank href="http://home2.pi.be/ping1796/cmied_home.htm">The Cognitive Mechanics of Economic Development and Institutional Change</a>", started 1998, defended 2004.  (co-promotor with M. Despontin).<Dt><b>Leor Gr&uuml;ndlinger</b> (computer science, Israel): <Dd>started 1999, stopped 2001, subject "Collective intelligence in on-line election markets"</dl></nodetxt><p><p><p><HR WIDTH=420><font size=-1><a href="/COPYR.html">Copyright&copy; 2008 Principia Cybernetica</a> - <a href="REFERPCP.html">Referencing this page</a></TD></TR></TABLE></CENTER></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH=140 BGCOLOR=DED6A5><TABLE WIDTH=100% CELLPADDING=15 BORDER=0 CELLSPACING=0 BGCOLOR=FFF5CB><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>      <BR>   <B> <FONT FACE="ARIAL, HELVETICA, SANS-SERIF" SIZE=-1>Author</FONT></B><br>  <FONT SIZE=-1> <author>F. <a rev=made href="HEYL.html">Heylighen</a>, </author></FONT><p>   <B> <FONT FACE="ARIAL, HELVETICA, SANS-SERIF" SIZE=-1>Date</FONT></B>   <BR><FONT SIZE=-1><update>Mar 26, 2008</update> (modified)<br><create>Jan 27, 2004</create> (created)</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>   <TABLE CELLPADDING=10 BORDER=0><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP>      <CENTER>   <FONT FACE="ARIAL, HELVETICA, SANS-SERIF " SIZE=-1>    <a href=/DEFAULT.html>Home</a><br><img src=/Images/up.gif><br><FONT SIZE=-1><a href=/ORG.html>Project Organization</a><br><img src=/Images/up.gif><br><a href=/CONTR.html>Contributing to the Principia Cybernetica Project</a><br><img src=/Images/up.gif><br><a href=/PEOPLE.html>List of contributors</a><br><img src=/Images/up.gif><br><parent><a href=/HEYL.html>Francis Heylighen: home page</a></parent></FONT>      </FONT>      <P><B>    <FONT FACE="ARIAL, HELVETICA, SANS-SERIF" SIZE=-1>     Up      <BR>      <A HREF="/HEYL.html">Prev.</A>      <img src="/Images/4arrows.gif" width="37" height="36" align="middle">      <a HREF="/HEYBIO.html">Next</A>      <BR>   Down   </FONT>   </B>       </CENTER><HR><P>     <FONT FACE="ARIAL, HELVETICA, SANS-SERIF" SIZE=-1>      </FONT>      </TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=BOTTOM WIDTH=140 BGCOLOR=DED6A5>   <CENTER><P><HR align="left" noshade><a href="/MAKANNOT.html">Discussion</a><HR></CENTER>              <FONT SIZ